description: Number of partitions of n such that cn(0,5) = cn(2,5) < cn(1,5) = cn(3,5) = cn(4,5).
comments: Also, number of partitions of n such that cn(3,5) = cn(4,5) < cn(0,5) = cn(1,5) = cn(2,5).For a given partition, cn(i,n) means the number of its parts equal to i modulo n.
